   ↳ com.google.android.apps.auto.sdk.notification.CarNotificationExtender

Class Overview

Allows apps to add Android Auto extensions to notifications.

To create a notification with this Extender:

  1. Create a NotificationCompat.Builder and set desired properties.
  2. Create a CarNotificationExtender.
  3. Set car-specific properties using the add and set methods of CarNotificationExtender.
  4. Call extend(NotificationCompat.Builder) to apply the extensions to a notification.
  5. Post the notification to the notification system with the NotificationManagerCompat.notify(...) methods (do not use the NotificationManager.notify(...) methods). 
 Notification notification = new NotificationCompat.Builder(context, channelId)
         ...
         .extend(new CarNotificationExtender.Builder()
                 .set*(...)
                 .build())
         .build();
To access car extensions on an existing notification, use the CarNotificationExtender(Notification) constructor then use get methods to access values.

Constants

public static final int TYPE_NAVIGATION

TYPE_NAVIGATION notification is a turn-by-turn notification that usually has three text fields. When constructing a notification with CarNotificationExtender.Builder, setTitle(CharSequence) sets the name of next turn road or direction, e.g. "Head South" or "Charleston Rd". setSubtitle(CharSequence) sets the distance to the next turn with unit, e.g. "150 ft" or "12 mi". setText(CharSequence) sets the formatted destination ETA, e.g. "Arrive at 4:15 PM".

Constant Value: 1 (0x00000001)

public static final int TYPE_NORMAL

TYPE_NORMAL notification is the default type that doesn't support the third text field. Calling setText(CharSequence) doesn't have any effect for this type of notification.

Constant Value: 0 (0x00000000)
